<h2>Organizational Minutes - Ixion Biotechnology</h2>
<PRE>Contributor: Weaver Gaines
Firm: Ixion Biotechnology
Address: One Progress Blvd, Box 26
Alachua, FL 32615
Telephone: (904) 462-3961
Fax: (904) 462-5261
E-mail: <a href=mailto:wgainesn@counsel.com>wgainesn@counsel.com</a>
Editor's note: Here is an example of "organizational minutes."
See also, board retainer plan. 
* * * 
   XYZ, INC.
   ORGANIZATION MINUTES (DELAWARE COMPANY)
   ACTION BY UNANIMOUS WRITTEN CONSENT 
   OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS
Pursuant to Section 141(f) of the Delaware Corporation Law,
and in accordance with Article II, Section 7 of the Bylaws, we
the undersigned, constituting the complete membership of the
Board of Directors of XYZ, Inc., a Delaware corporation (the
"Company") hereby consent to the following action to have the
same force as action taken at a duly called and held meeting
of the Board of Directors.
   BYLAWS
   RESOLVED, that the Bylaws in the form adopted by the
incorporator of the Company and annexed hereto are in all
respects approved and adopted as the Bylaws of the Company.
   OFFICERS   
   RESOLVED, that the following individuals are elected to
serve as officers of the Company, effective immediately, and
that said individuals will serve in such capacities at a
compensation, if any, established by the Board of Directors,
for a term of one year, or until their successor is duly
chosen, qualified, and elected.
          Name       				__________________________                   
          
          Office     				__________________________              
         
          President  				__________________________
      
          Secretary and Treasurer   __________________________
          
   ANNUAL MEETING
   RESOLVED, that the date of the first annual meeting of the
shareholders of the Company shall be held at _________________
, on the first Tuesday in May of each year at such hour as may
be stated in the notice of such meeting.
   CORPORATE SEAL
   RESOLVED, that the form of corporate seal, the impression
of which is affixed on the last page of this consent, is
approved as the corporate seal of the Company.
   SHARE CERTIFICATE
   RESOLVED, that the form of share certificate for fully paid
and non-assessable shares of stock of the Company, a copy of
which is attached to this consent, is approved, and that a
specimen of such certificate be annexed to these minutes.
   ISSUANCE OF SHARES
   RESOLVED, that the Board of Directors is authorized in its
discretion to issue the shares of the Company to the full
number of shares authorized by the Certificate of
Incorporation in such number and for such consideration as
from time to time shall be determined by the Board of
Directors and as may be permitted by law.
   
   ISSUING SHARES FOR CASH
   WHEREAS, Mr. ___________________, of [City and State], has
offered to purchase      shares of the Company, and to pay the
sum of $ ___________ in cash for such share, it is 
   RESOLVED, that the Company is prepared to issue stock to
Mr. ____________________, subject to the following restrictions: that
all shares shall be issued for investment only, and not for
resale; and
   FURTHER RESOLVED, that pursuant to section 152 of the
General Corporation Law, the Board hereby determines that $
per share is adequate consideration for a share of common
stock of the Company; and
   FURTHER RESOLVED, the offer of Mr. ___________________is accepted,
and that, upon receipt of the subscription price, the proper
officers of the Company are directed to execute, issue, and
deliver in the name and on behalf of the Company, and under
its corporate seal, a certificate for                fully-
paid and nonassessable restricted shares of the Company to the
order of Mr.                 ;  such certificate to have
stamped or typed on the face or back (so long as they are
subject to restriction) the following legend:
      "Notice:  This stock acquired for investment only, and
not for resale. " 
   FURTHER RESOLVED, pursuant to section 154 of the General
Corporation Law, an amount equal to the aggregate par value of
the                  shares referred to in the next preceding
resolution, or $ __________shall be capital and the
remainder shall be additional paid in capital; and
   GENERAL LICENSING AUTHORITY
   RESOLVED, that the proper officers of the Company are
authorized and directed on behalf of the Company, to make and
file such certificate or certificates, report or reports, or
other instrument or instruments as may be required by law to
be filed with the federal government (including, without
limitation, an application for a tax identification number),
or in any state, territory, or dependency of the United
States, or in any foreign country in which said officers shall
find it necessary or expedient to file the same to authorize
the Company to transact business.
   BANK RESOLUTION
   RESOLVED, the Treasurer of the Company is authorized and
directed to open a bank account with such bank as such officer
shall determine to be in the interests of the Company; and
   FURTHER RESOLVED, that the resolutions prescribed and
furnished by the said bank for opening said account and for
designating the officers to sign drafts and checks thereon are
adopted and made a part of this consent.
          
   THIS CONSENT may be signed in counterparts, each of which
shall be considered an original and all of which together
shall constitute one original.
Dated:   ______________
                                                               
Director __________________________               
</PRE>
