<HEAD>
<TITLE>Court TV Legal Helpline Info</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<A HREF="/map/helpline.map/"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/helpline.gif" ALT="Legal Helpline" ISMAP BORDER="0"></A>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>

<H2>About the Legal Helpline</H2>

<P>We're pleased to welcome you to the Legal Helpline, our new service that gives non-lawyers a place to ask experienced attorneys for information about everyday legal situations.</P>

<P>It's important that you understand that the Legal Helpline won't be a substitute for hiring a lawyer to represent you or give you advice about your particular situation. But it is a great way to get background on legal issues that affect your life, learn about the law and the justice system, and help you decide whether you need a lawyer and what to ask the lawyer if you hire one.</P>

<P>Submit your question through our e-mail submission form, and it will be answered by <A HREF="/legalhelp/helpline/panelists.html">members</A> of the Law Center Bar Association. These are lawyers who are also members of <A HREF="http://www.counsel.com/inside/">Counsel Connect</A>, the largest online service exclusively for lawyers, and have agreed to make themselves available to you.</P>

<P>You'll probably see a lot of postings from Parry Aftab, the host of the Court TV Law Center Legal Helpline. Parry is a lawyer in New Jersey and New York who has been hosting online legal discussions for several years, and we're lucky to have her.</P>

<P>If you are a lawyer and would like to join the LCBA, please e-mail Court TV Law Center Editor Craig Matters at <A HREF="mailto:comments@courttv.com">comments@courttv.com</A>.</P>

<P>We hope you find the Legal Helpline useful. If you have comments or criticisms, please <A HREF="/comments/">let us know</A>.</P>

<P>Craig Matters<BR>
Editor<BR>
Court TV Law Center</P>

<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=LEFT>
<IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/rights2.gif" ALT="Copyright 1996 by American Lawyer Media, L.P. All Rights Reserved.">
