<TITLE>Court TV Legal Helpline: Panelists</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#000080" VLINK="#DD0000">
<IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/graphics/ctv/headers/helpline.gif">
<H2>Legal Helpline Host</H2>

<P><B>PARRY AFTAB</B><BR>

<A HREF="mailto:paftab01@counsel.com">paftab01@counsel.com</A><BR>

<A HREF="mailto:parrya@aol.com">parrya@aol.com</A><BR>

Parry, a partner in the firm of Aftab & Savitt, P.C., specializes in U.S. business law and has extensive international commercial law experience. She has recently been selected as a founding director to the Bulgarian American Investment Council and holds the power-of-attorney for both Moscow Legal Center and Russian Lawyers Guild in the U.S. In addition, Parry has been a featured speaker at international legal conferences on Doing Business in Russia and on International Human Rights and participated in the Mid-Decade United Nations Conference on Women in the World on issues relating to women in the Middle East. She is a graduate of New York University School of Law.</P>



<HR WIDTH=525 ALIGN=CENTER><BR>

<H2>Legal Helpline Panelists</H2>




<P><B>GUY ALVAREZ</B><BR>

<A HREF="mailto:galvarez@counsel.com">galvarez@counsel.com</A><BR>

<A HREF="mailto:guylaw@aol.com">guylaw@aol.com</A><BR>

Guy, an associate with the New York law firm of Wasserman, Schneider & Babb, practices international law, with a focus on trade and investment matters in Mexico, Latin America and the Caribbean. He has written several articles on NAFTA and its effect on regional and global trade. Guy is also the owner of the FORINTLAW listserv, a mailing list for the discussion of substantive international law. He is currently working on an article on the use of the Internet in international trade. Guy graduated from Brooklyn Law School and received a bachelor's degree from the University of Massachusetts.</P>


<P><B>WILLIAM ARNOLD</B><br>

<A HREF="mailto:warnol00@counsel.com">warnol00@counsel.com</a><BR>


<P><B>MICHAEL ASSAF</B><BR>

<A HREF="mailto:massaf@counsel.com">massaf@counsel.com</A><BR>

<A HREF="mailto:counse616@aol.com">counse616@aol.com</A><BR>

