<H2>Death and Divorce</H2>

<P><B>Massachusetts Family Law<BR>
Sponsored by: <A HREF="sooho.html">Law Offices of Sharyn T. Sooho</A></B></P>

<P>Divorce invalidates any provisions you made in your will for your former spouse, unless you make an explicit exception. Be sure to review and update wills after divorce. Also review:</P>
<UL>
<LI>life insurance policies
<LI>IRA's and other retirement plans
<LI>trusts
<LI>employee benefits
<LI>deeds
<LI>bank accounts
<LI>stock certificates
<LI>all certificates of title 
</UL>

<P>For additional information please contact us at (617) 969-1400 or <A HREF="mailto:STS@DivorceNet.com">STS@DivorceNet.com</A>.

