<HtMl><head><title> Court TV Law Center Q & A</title></head><BODY BGCOLOR=ffffff VLINK=FF0005><P align=center><img width=400 height=60 src=/graphics/ctv/qanda/qanda3.gif></P><H3 align=center> Using Mediation to Handle Your Divorce</H3><h3>2. Why would I want to mediate my divorce?</h3><blockquote>Traditionally, when a couple is considering divorce, each hires his andher own lawyer. The lawyers then try to work out the terms of asettlement -- with letters, phone calls, legal documents and courthearings. If the lawyers and parties don't agree, they take the case totrial in court.<p>The advantage of this adversarial system -- each attorney trying to getas much as possible for his client -- is that both husband and wife havethe help of a knowledgeable legal expert who's doing everything possibleto protect that party's interests.<p>The downside of this system is that it's expensive and tends to increaseany existing tension between the parties, who often end up angrier ateach other than when they began. Their children may also be caught up inthe conflict and injured by it. The adversarial court system assumesthat the parties are enemies; this assumption can be very destructivewhen applied to families.<p>If conflict escalates, so does the cost. The attorney's meetings withyou, possible witnesses, and experts; telephone calls; letters; hearings-- it all adds up to a lot of attorney time and a lot of expense.<p>Mediation can drastically reduce both the hostility and the cost of yourdivorce. It also gives you the power to make your own decisions --rather than allow lawyers and judges to make them. And it gives youprivacy; the discussions are in your mediator's office, not a publiccourtroom.</blockquote></P><P><B><I>Any answers posted are for your information only and are not intended toconstitute legal advice.</I></B></P><P><a href=/legalhelp/qanda/james/index.html#tab><B><I>Main Page</I></B></a><P><P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/stroke.gif" HEIGHT=15 WIDTH=547><BR><A HREF="/map/bottom.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bottom.gif" ISMAP ALIGN=ABSBOTTOM BORDER=0 WIDTH=533 HEIGHT=30></A><BR><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/rights.gif" ALT="Copyright 1995 by the Courtroom Television Network. All Rights Reserved. No parts of this site may be reproduced in any form without permission of Court TV. Disclaimer: Nothing in this site is intended to constitute legal advice"></P></BODY></HTML> 
