<HtMl><head><title> Court TV Law Center Q & A</title></head><BODY BGCOLOR=ffffff VLINK=FF0005><P align=center><img width=400 height=60 src=/graphics/ctv/qanda/qanda3.gif></P><H3 align=center> Using Mediation to Handle Your Divorce</H3><h3>3. What does a mediated divorce look like?</h3><blockquote>The two of you together meet with the mediator, who guides you throughthe legal issues in your divorce and helps you reach agreements. If yourmediator is an experienced family law attorney, she'll be familiar withthe legal issues that need to be addressed and will help you considerthe various options available to you. She may even draft the necessarypaperwork.<p>When you begin mediation, you may be angry with each other or you may befriendly. You may have agreed on all the issues or on none of them. Itdoesn't matter. The mediator will take you where she finds you and helpyou reach informed, reasonable agreements. She keeps you on track, helpsyou listen to each other, brings up legal issues you may not havethought of, and helps you work through the rough spots and still reachagreements.<p>Sometimes couples decide to try mediation after they've already begunlitigation. They've hired attorneys and possibly had hearings or begunformal discovery. Mediation is still a good way to avoid escalating yourlawsuit further. You can mediate at anytime -- even the day before yougo to court.<p>If you've both retained attorneys, you'll probably bring those lawyerswith you to the mediation session to help you evaluate the other side'soffers and propose counter-offers. Although this method is moreexpensive because you're paying your lawyers as well as the mediator,it's still far less expensive than trying your case in court.</blockquote></P><P><B><I>Any answers posted are for your information only and are not intended toconstitute legal advice.</I></B></P><P><a href=/legalhelp/qanda/james/index.html#tab><B><I>Main Page</I></B></a><P><P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/stroke.gif" HEIGHT=15 WIDTH=547><BR><A HREF="/map/bottom.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bottom.gif" ISMAP ALIGN=ABSBOTTOM BORDER=0 WIDTH=533 HEIGHT=30></A><BR><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/rights.gif" ALT="Copyright 1995 by the Courtroom Television Network. All Rights Reserved. No parts of this site may be reproduced in any form without permission of Court TV. Disclaimer: Nothing in this site is intended to constitute legal advice"></P></BODY></HTML> 
