<HtMl><head><title> Court TV Law Center Q & A</title></head><BODY BGCOLOR=ffffff VLINK=FF0005><P align=center><img width=400 height=60 src=/graphics/ctv/qanda/qanda3.gif alt="COURT TV LAW CENTER Q & A"></P><H3 align=center>Living Wills</H3><blockquote><font size=+2><B>Q:</B></font> I made a living will a few years ago. Since this area of the law is new and evolving, do I have to do anything special to make sure my living will is up to date?<P><font size=+2><B>A:</B></font> The best thing to do is to look at it to make sure it still reflects what you want. Talk it over with your doctor. Changing medical technology, changing personal health, and changing laws each may play a part in whether you want to change your living will. The most important thing is to make sure what you have in writing is a clear expression of your wishes.</blockquote></P><P><B><I>Any answers posted are for your information only and are not intended toconstitute legal advice.</I></B></P><P><a href=/legalhelp/qanda/hurme/index.html#tab><B><I>Main Page</I></B></a><P><P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/stroke.gif" HEIGHT=15 WIDTH=547><BR><A HREF="/map/bottom.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/bottom.gif" ISMAP ALIGN=ABSBOTTOM BORDER=0 WIDTH=533 HEIGHT=30></A><BR><IMG SRC="/graphics/ctv/rights.gif" ALT="Copyright 1995 by the Courtroom Television Network. All Rights Reserved. No parts of this site may be reproduced in any form without permission of Court TV. Disclaimer: Nothing in this site is intended to constitute legal advice"></P></BODY></HTML> 
