<HEAD>
<TITLE>Killing Time: Ordering Information</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FF0000" VLINK="#FF0000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">

<P ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="mactop.gif" ALIGN=TOP BORDER="0"><BR><BR>
<FONT SIZE="+3"><B>Killing Time</B></FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="+1"><I>by Donald Freed</I></FONT></P>

<UL><P>The Trial of the Century is over, but the murder mystery remains...Did O.J. Do It?<IMG SRC="cover.gif" ALIGN=RIGHT WIDTH="80" HEIGHT="100" BORDER="0" VSPACE="10" HSPACE="20"></P>

<P>This compelling investigation into the unsolved murders of Nicole Brown Simpson and Ronald Goldman focuses on the literal timeframe when the murders occurred--the "killing time," sometime between 10 and 11 p.m., June 12, 1994. In a groundbreaking scientific forensic investigation, material from the crime scene is analyzed to produce different scenarios of the murders, each with its own timeline of evidence and players.</P>

<P>Author Donald Freed finds the perfect blend of suspense and inquiry as he takes us through each retelling of the murders, beginning with the partisan theories of the prosecution and defense, and why each is flawed. Woven throughout are explosive information, interviews, and countless signs of both conspiracy and cover-up. From what the lawyers didn't tell you and the press didn't report; to insights from a "deep throat" source; to organized crime and drugs in Brentwood, <B><I>Killing Time</I></B> will make you reassess what you thought you knew and explore areas you never imagined, such as:</P>

<UL TYPE=DISC>
	<LI>Who left the evidence found in Nicole's garage?
	<LI>What happened to the prosecution's double assassin theory?
	<LI>Who was Nicole's other gentleman caller that night?
	<LI>Why was the constellation of murders around Ronald Goldman not explored?
	<LI>Could Ron have been the target?
</UL>

<P>Is the case open or closed? For those wanting to develop their own scenario, shocking new leads and a blank timeline are provided. In the pages of this public "court," scores of questions are left for you to answer, because you are the jury.</P>

<HR WIDTH=300 NOSHADE><BR>

<P>To purchase the book now at a 20% discount, <A HREF="http://www.mcp.com/cgi-bin/placeorder?express=0-02-861340-6">click here</A> and enter code CC20 as your MacMillan account number. You must use this code to receive the special 20% discount for Court TV Law Center users.</P>

<P>You may also order by calling 800-428-5311 and mentioning the discount code to the operator.</P>

<P>For more information on the book, visit the <A HREF="http://www.mcp.com/mgr/killingtime/">MacMillan Publishing website</A>.</P>
</UL>
</BODY>
</HTML>
