Q: Anybody else besides Vannatter and you in the car? 
 
A: If it would have been, it would have been police officers. 
 
Q: When you got --You went directly from Rockingham to the 
police station. Correct. 
 
A: Correct. 
 
Q: And then you went to a room-- 
 
A: Yes. 
 
Q: --with Vannatter? 
 
A: Yes. I believe Vannatter or Lange. At the time I wasn't 
registering who they were. 
 
Q: When you got to the police station, Mr. Simpson, you went 
directly to this room. Right? 
 
A: Yes. 
 
Q: No stops in between. Correct? 
 
A: I don't recall. 
 
Q: When you got to the room, who was there? 
 
A: They were there and some other guys were coming in and out, I 
gather police officers, and then at one point my lawyers came in, 
and they left the room. 
 
Q: "They" being whom? 
 
 A: Whatever police officers were there. 
 
Q: You don't remember? 
 
A: No 
 
Q: Now, did you have a discussion with-- Was Lange in the room, 
too? 
 
A: You know, there were guys coming in and out, so I can't really--
I couldn't register that at this point. 
 
Q: I will get back to that. In the car with Vannatter, was he in the 
back seat with you? 
 
A: I don't think so, but I really don't remember. I don't recall. 
 
Q: You were in the back seat. Right?  
 
A: Yes, I was in the back seat. 
 
Q: He was in the front seat.? 
 
A: Yes, I believe so. 
 
Q: And he asked you questions about the facts and circumstances 
surrounding Nicole's death? 
 
A: Yes. He was saying, "We got some problems," basically, and he 
was talking. 
 
Q: Have you ever seen any written statement of the discussion you 
