went. And I began to talk to her, and she was--she was relentless. 
She'd show up at the golf course, and it began to be a problem. 
So my mother told me I should, you know, get alone with her and 
find out exactly what it was-- what was happening with her.  I 
spoke with her mother.  And Nicole just told me she loved me and 
she hated what was going on in her life, and she wanted to get back 
with me, and for the kids she wanted us to get back together. And I 
told her that I'd start--okay once a week we'd start having dinner 
together with the kids and--but that didn't help, because she then 
began to show up at the golf course with her girlfriends and started 
