A: I told her to "Just be yourself. You're gorgeous.  What is there 
for him not to like, plus you ain't gonna cost him a dime." 
 
Q: Why is that? 
 
A: Because she was getting plenty of money from me. 
 
Q: Now, by this time had you met Paula? 
 
A: Actually, I met Paula two days after this. 
 
Q: So you still wanted to get back with Nicole when she came to 
talk to you about Joseph. Right? 
 
A: I would have, yes. I would have. 
 
Q: But you told her to do what she wanted. Right? 
 
A: No. I gave her the best advice I can give her. She found a guy 
who she liked, and if your wife told you that there's a guy that she 
was crazy about, I think you would move on, and that's what I did. 
 
Q: Did she tell you about any other men besides Joseph, Alejandro 
and Keith? 
 
A: As I said, the Keith thing wasn't a matter of telling me about it, 
and Joseph was a guy that she told me about, yes. 
 
Q: And you mentioned Alejandro. 
 
A: Yes, but I had knew about Alejandro. 
 
Q: What about a guy named Brett Shaves? 
 
A: I don't think he was in her life at this point in time. 
 
Q: I am talking about all the way up until 1994 when she died. 
 
A: Okay. Brett Shaves I found out about at one of our divorce 
hearings. 
 
Q: First time you found out about it? 
 
A: Yeah. 
 
Q: And was that the only--last time you talked to Nicole about 
