A: I played golf with him, so I'm sure he was in town. 
 
Q: And to the best of your knowledge, the subject of he and Nicole 
being together never came up. Is that right? 
 
A: Yes, that's correct. 
 
Q: There was a time in late--there was a time in May 1994 when 
you and Nicole ended your attempted reconciliation. Right? 
 
A: When I ended our reconciliation. 
 
Q: Why do you say you as opposed to both of you? 
 
A: Because I told her I couldn't do it anymore. 
 
Q: It was your decision, not hers? 
 
A: Yes, that's correct. I told her, "I gave it a year, the year's up, and 
I can't do it anymore." 
 
Q: And you at that time felt like you were; free and unattached 
from her. Correct? 
 
A: Yes. 
 
MR. BAKER: You mean romantically as contrasted to the mother 
