A: I talked to him, but not to find out if he was seeing her again. 
 
Q: You talked to him about what? 
 
A: Well, he was a friend and he'd call, and I talked to his wife often 
from jail, Katherine, and when it came out that Nicole and he had 
had a relationship, I talked to Katherine a few times to kind of help 
her through it. 
 
Q: When is the first time you spoke to Marcus Allen after Nicole's 
death? 
 
A: He came to jail once, I guess, and he may have called--he and 
Katherine may have called that week from where they were. 
 
Q: That was the first time? 
 
A: The first week that I was--after the murder and the first week of 
the murder, I assume so.  So many people were calling me, I'm just 
assuming Katherine and Marc called--Marcus called during that 
time. 
 
