A: I spent the night with Nicole. 
 
Q: Did you tell her then that you wanted to stop the relationship? 
 
A: The next day I told her that I thought we need to go to therapy, 
and I needed her to go--I wanted her to go back to whatever she 
was going to. When she asked me to come back in the relationship, 
she prefaced all of that with the therapy she was going to and how 
it had helped her, and I suggested that she try that again and-- 
 
Q: With you? 
 
A: With me, without me, whatever. 
 
Q: And what did she say? 
 
A: She didn't know. She wanted-- she thought whatever the 
problem was, it was just--I think she kinda blamed it on her 
friends. She was l trying to help Faye with her drugs, help Cora 
with whatever she was going through with her husband, I and-- but 
as I said right before I came back from Puerto Rico--she had said 
"OJ., I'm sorry?" She apologized for the whole time I was there. 
She said, "I want to pick you up at the airport," which she did.  So I 
was sorta at a place where I'll try it, but I really kind of wanted out, 
and by the end of the week I totally wanted out. 
 
Q: W hat happened that week to cause you to make that decision? 
 
A: Saturday we were about to go to dinner, and she almost had a 
nervous breakdown. 
 
Q: Saturday when? 
 
A: Saturday in Laguna, probably about the 7th or 8th of May. 
 
Q: Before Mother's Day? 
 
A: The day before Mother's Day. And even though she was very--
she was fine on Mother's Day, the night before it was just too 
weird for me. 
 
Q:  What happened that night? 
 
